4.5. Apply NMSTATE NNCP policies
REF : Chapter 8. Network requirements | Planning your deployment | Red Hat OpenShift Data Foundation | 4.18 | Red Hat Documentation

the logic of having the NNCP policies is to have a MACVLAN interface on which MULTUS is configured for ODF. Now, the MACVLAN can be on top of a single interface or a bonded interface. Additionally, in VVT (Suwon) setups, there is a requirement of having a VLAN interface on top of bond/single interface. So, PLEASE check the network plan and requirements and proceed accordingly. The NNCP YAMLs for all type of configurations are provided below (these are examples, please choose the interface names and IPs correctly).



The different configurations are as below :

 single interface → MACVLAN
 single interface → VLAN → MACVLAN
 two interfaces → bond interface → MACVLAN
 two interfaces → bond interface → VLAN → MACVLAN




4.5.1.  create NNCP policies on a single interface (single interface → MACVLAN)
create separate NNCP policies for master nodes


# create separate NNCP policies for master nodes, on a single NW interface
Redhat Guidelines:
For static IP management, each node must have a different NodeNetworkConfigurationPolicy.
Select separate nodes for each policy to configure static networks.
A “shim” interface is used to connect hosts to the Multus public network using the same technology as the Network Attachment Definition will use.
The host’s “shim” must be of the same type as planned for pods, macvlan here.
The interface must match the Multus public network interface selected in planning, ens4f1 in this example.
The ipv4 section configures node IP addresses on the Multus public network.
IPs assigned to this node’s shim must match the plan. This example uses 110.200.63.0/22 for node IPs on the Multus public network.
For static IP management, don’t forget to change the IP for each node.
The routes section instructs nodes how to reach pods on the Multus public network.



srib@ocp-haproxy-4:~/ocp-configMNO$ cat nncp-odf-master1.yaml
apiVersion: nmstate.io/v1
kind: NodeNetworkConfigurationPolicy
metadata:
  name: odf-pub-shim-master1 
spec:
  nodeSelector:
    kubernetes.io/hostname: master1.lab4.srib-lab-ocp.lan
    node-role.kubernetes.io/master: ""
  desiredState:
    interfaces:
      - name: odf-pub-shim         
        description: "ODF public shim"
        type: mac-vlan
        state: up
        mac-vlan:
          base-iface: ens4f1
          mode: bridge
          promiscuous: true
        ipv4:
          enabled: true
          dhcp: false
          address:
            - ip: 10.200.63.2
              prefix-length: 24
    routes:
      config:
        - destination: 10.200.63.0/24
          next-hop-interface: odf-pub-shim
